        <section>
            <title>Format Information</title>
            <para>This documentation is written in DocBook 5.2 XML format. DocBook is a standard for technical documentation that can be converted to multiple output formats:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem><para>HTML — Web-based documentation</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>PDF — Printable format</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>EPUB — E-book format</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Man pages — Unix manual pages</para></listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>Building Documentation from XML</title>
            <para>To generate output formats from the DocBook XML files, use DocBook tools:</para>

            <section>
                <title>Generate HTML</title>
                <screen>xsltproc --output opcgw-user-manual.html \
  /usr/share/xml/docbook/stylesheet/docbook-xsl/html/docbook.xsl \
  opcgw-user-manual.xml</screen>
            </section>

            <section>
                <title>Generate PDF</title>
                <screen>fop -xml opcgw-user-manual.xml \
  -xsl /usr/share/xml/docbook/stylesheet/docbook-xsl/fo/docbook.xsl \
  -pdf opcgw-user-manual.pdf</screen>
            </section>

            <section>
                <title>Generate EPUB</title>
                <screen>pandoc --from docbook --to epub \
  --output opcgw-user-manual.epub \
  opcgw-user-manual.xml</screen>
            </section>
        </section>

